data.title: Covered Bridges of California
data.text:
HONEY RUN GRADE BRIDGE 05-04-01, Pratt & Kingpost Trusses, built in 1896, was located East of Chico just off Honey Run Road. It was a casualty of the November 2018 Camp Fire.

The GPS location is N39 43.706 W121 42.211. CASTLEBERRY BRIDGE 05-04-B, Stringer, built in 1984, is located South of Cherokee on Oregon Gulch (Derrick) Road .

The GPS location is N39 35.627 W121 31.782. BRIDGEPORT BRIDGE 05-29-01, Howe Truss w/Arch, built in 1862, is located WNW of Nevada City, off Pleasant Valley Road.

The GPS location is N39 17.568 W121 11.969. FELTON BRIDGE 05-44-02, Modified Pratt Truss, built in 1892, is located in Felton Covered Bridge Park, off Covered Bridge Road.

The GPS location is N37 03.345 W122 04.259. PARADISE PARK BRIDGE 05-44-03, Smith Truss, built in 1872, is located in Masonic Paradise Park in North Santa Cruz.

The GPS location is N37 00.49 W122 02.67.
